# Single source of truth for the Grafana Cloud OTLP/Loki ingest endpoints. (#785)
#
# NON-SECRET base URLs for the shared free-tier Grafana Cloud stack. Staging and
# production point at the SAME stack, so these values are IDENTICAL across
# environments — only the per-environment auth-header *secret* names differ, and
# those live in GCP Secret Manager, never here.
#
# This file is `source`d by .github/workflows/deploy.yml and drives BOTH collector
# topologies, so every consumer derives its endpoints from here:
#   - Cloud Run sidecar    -> exported to scripts/inject-otel-sidecar.py as
#                             OTEL_OTLP_ENDPOINT / OTEL_LOKI_ENDPOINT
#   - GKE DaemonSet (Helm) -> passed to `helm upgrade` via
#                             --set-string env.OTEL_COLLECTOR_OTLP_ENDPOINT / _LOKI_ENDPOINT
#
# Because every consumer reads this file, a region/gateway change — the drift that
# caused the no-telemetry incident #781 — is now a ONE-LINE edit here.
# scripts/check-grafana-endpoint-sources.mjs (CI) fails the build if a literal
# endpoint URL is re-hardcoded in any other config file.
#
# When changing these, verify against the live stack:
#   Grafana Cloud -> Stack -> Details ->
#     OpenTelemetry -> OTLP endpoint    (traces + metrics -> Tempo / Mimir)
#     Loki -> URL, with /otlp appended  (logs -> Loki, native OTLP ingestion)
export OTEL_OTLP_ENDPOINT=https://otlp-gateway-prod-us-east-3.grafana.net/otlp
export OTEL_LOKI_ENDPOINT=https://logs-prod-042.grafana.net/otlp
